Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
init_enable_drc_region_layer(25.10)        init_enable_drc_region_layer(25.10)

Name
       init_enable_drc_region_layer

Syntax
        init_enable_drc_region_layer {<list_of_drc_region_layer>}

       Type: String

       Default: ""

       Specifies  a  list of drc_region_layer to restore the active DRC region
       layer.  The  init_enable_drc_region_layer  global  is   saved   through
       saveDesign in the *.global file.

       init_enable_drc_region_layer {M1_FB1, M2_FB1}

       LAYER M1_FB1

       TYPE ROUTING ;

       PROPERTY LEF58_REGION "REGION FB1 BASEDLAYER Metal1 ;" ;

       WIDTH 0.460 ;

       MINWIDTH 0.230 ;

       MAXWIDTH 0.60 ;

       SPACING 0.230 ;

       SPACING 0.6 RANGE 10.0 100000.0 ;

       PITCH 0.560 ;

       DIRECTION HORIZONTAL ;

       END M1_FB1

       Tool  loads  only  the  DRC  region  layer which is defined in init_en-
       able_drc_region_layer.

       If the base layer (Metal3) only has one DRC region layer(M3_FB1) and is
       not defined in init_enable_drc_region_layer, the tool loads the DRC re-
       gion  layer  without  showing  any  message.  However,  if   the   base
       layer(Metal3)  has  multiple  DRC region layers(M3_FB1, M3_FB6) and are
       not defined in init_enable_drc_region_layer, the tool will give a warn-
       ing message and load the first DRC region layer.

Related Information
